It has been reported that <termsem="GO:0022610"> adhesion </term> molecules , such as <termsem="GO:0007158"> neural cell adhesion </term> molecule ( NCAM ) , are not only implicated in cell interactions during <termsem="GO:0007399"> nervous system development </term> , but are also recognised as important mediators of synaptic plasticity in the adult nervous system [ 35 ] .
